sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant App as Service
  participant DB as Postgres
  participant WAL as WAL / replication slot
  participant Deb as Debezium connector
  participant Reg as Schema Registry
  participant K as Kafka
  App->>DB: BEGIN
  App->>DB: UPDATE orders SET status='PLACED'
  App->>DB: INSERT INTO outbox (aggregate_id, event_type, payload, headers)
  App->>DB: COMMIT
  DB-->>WAL: append commit record
  Deb->>WAL: stream logical replication events
  Deb->>Reg: register / fetch schema for event_type
  Reg-->>Deb: schema id
  Deb->>K: publish (key=aggregate_id, headers, schema-id + payload)
  K-->>Deb: ack at offset
  Note over DB,K: Outbox row never re-read by polling. Cleanup is a separate TTL job.<br/>Order across aggregates is broker partition order.
